<!-- ── BELIEFS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="beliefs-list">
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>The Holy Scriptures</h4>
        <p>
          We believe the sixty-six books of the Old and New Testaments are given
          by divine inspiration and are the infallible written Word of God,
          superior to all human authority and containing all things necessary
          for our salvation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>The Holy Trinity</h4>
        <p>
          We believe there is one living and true God, everlasting and infinite,
          existing in three persons of one substance: the Father, the Son, and
          the Holy Spirit. The Father is creator, the Son is redeemer, and the
          Holy Spirit sanctifies and indwells believers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>Jesus Christ</h4>
        <p>
          We believe Jesus Christ, the eternal Son of God, was conceived by the
          Holy Spirit and born of the Virgin Mary, fully God and fully man. He
          was crucified for our sins, rose bodily from the dead, ascended into
          heaven, and now intercedes for us at the right hand of the Father.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>The Holy Spirit</h4>
        <p>
          We believe the Holy Spirit is fully God, ever present and active in
          the Church, convicting the world of sin, regenerating those who repent
          and believe, sanctifying believers, and guiding them into all truth.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>Original Sin and Salvation</h4>
        <p>
          We believe all people are sinners by nature and in need of God's grace.
          Jesus Christ made full atonement for all human sin through His death on
          the cross. Salvation is received through genuine repentance and faith in
          Jesus Christ, not by human merit or good works.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>Justification and Regeneration</h4>
        <p>
          We believe justification is God's gracious act of granting full pardon
          of guilt to all who believe on Jesus Christ. Regeneration is the work
          of the Holy Spirit by which the repentant sinner enters new spiritual
          life, delivered from the power of sin and adopted as a child of God.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>Entire Sanctification</h4>
        <p>
          We believe entire sanctification is a work of the Holy Spirit, subsequent
          to regeneration, by which the believer is cleansed from inbred sin and
          filled with the love of God. It is received by faith and empowers the
          believer for a life of service and obedience.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>The Sacraments</h4>
        <p>
          We believe Christ ordained two sacraments: Baptism and the Lord's Supper.
          Baptism is a sign of new birth and Christian profession. The Lord's Supper
          is a memorial of Christ's atoning death, a token of His coming again, and
          a means of grace for the faithful.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>Divine Healing</h4>
        <p>
          We believe in the Bible's teaching on divine healing and encourage our
          people to seek God in prayer for the healing of the sick, while also
          welcoming the use of medical means as provided by God's providence.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>The Return of Christ</h4>
        <p>
          We believe in the bodily, visible return of Jesus Christ, who will
          fulfill all prophecy and triumph over all evil. We also believe in the
          resurrection of the dead, the final judgment, and everlasting life for
          all who believe and follow Jesus Christ.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="belief-item">
        <h4>Marriage</h4>
        <p>
          We believe marriage was ordained by God as the mutual union of one man
          and one woman, intended for fellowship, love, and family. We encourage
          our people to enter marriage prayerfully and to cherish it as a sacred
          covenant.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

